news.title: Tamil Nadu to unveil mega sports city on East Coast Road; 500 acres identified
news.para: A 500-acre Rs 700-crore mega sports city is set to take shape on the city outskirts, with such swanky facilities like finest athletic tracks, indoor cycling velodrome, hockey stadium, multipurpose indoor stadium for basketball, volleyball and boxing.

news.title: China Evergrande targets restructuring proposal within six months as state tightens control
news.para: Once China's top developer, Evergrande has racked up debts of more than $300 billion and is struggling to repay creditors, suppliers and investors in wealth management products.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to issue notices to property tax defaulters
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Gaurav Gupta, who tested positive for Covid, held a virtual meeting to discuss property tax collection on Wednesday.

news.title: ESR acquires around eight acres of land in Delhi from TARC
news.para: The Indian warehousing segment has attracted large institutional investors, allocating fresh capital to the warehousing segment as demand continues to be strong from e-commerce and logistic firms and easing of policies, including the GST reform.

news.title: Noida: 416 housing plots up for grabs near Jewar airport site
news.para: The plots range from 120-500 sqm and 1,000-4,000 sqm, while the asking circle rate is between Rs 17,400 and Rs 17,800 a sqm.

news.title: China Evergrande to hold investor call on January 26: Sources
news.para: Evergrande, once China's top selling real estate developer, has more than $300 billion in liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of international bonds all deemed to be in default.

news.title: CHB yet to get fire NOC from Chandigarh civic body for IT park housing scheme
news.para: Recently, the urban planning and engineering departments of the administration had approved the plan to construct 728 flats in 16.6 acres of land of two pockets at IT Park at Rs 643 crore.

news.title: In two years, Chandigarh housing board got Rs 17.67 crore in online revenue
news.para: The board received maximum online collection in June last year when online collections reached Rs 2.21 crore. In February, the board earned Rs 1.32 crore, Rs 1.32 crore in March; Rs 1.51 crore in May; Rs 1.02 crore in July and Rs 1.94 crore in August 2021.

news.title: Nagpur civic body moots no tax for homes under 500 sq ft
news.para: NMC deputy commissioner Milind Meshram said, “There are likely over 2.5 lakh properties of 500 sq ft and below. Annual demand of these properties is around Rs30 crore per annum. Also, there is an arrears of Rs90 crore on these properties,” he said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: 95% of properties in nagarpalikas are illegal
news.para: The officials claim that the purpose of the sample survey of 8,000-odd buildings in the state is to help draft a legislation that will be a roadmap for every citizen to compulsorily get a BU permission for his/her property.

news.title: Council of engineers approaches Punjab governor over illegal buildings in Ludhiana
news.para: President of the association, Kapil Arora, informed that as per report prepared by the additional commissioner of MCL, there are 57,862 illegal buildings based on new electrical connections issued by PSPCL with respect to building plans approved and challans issued by MCL but this report is incomplete.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body teams visit flats to update property details, collect tax
news.para: The visits will help the MCC to update the database on properties in the city. The officials are visiting the apartments with a laptop, so that data can be updated, and the property tax can also be collected via online mode of payment.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body razes illegal constructions
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) on Tuesday demolished one residential and two industrial units that were illegally erected. The civic body also sealed three commercial units for lack of valid building use (BU) permission.

news.title: Nashik civic body chief seeks large residential project data
news.para: Jadhav gave the instructions following allegations by some parties that some plots meant for houses for economically weaker sections (EWS) were used for residential projects with commercial purposes.

news.title: Google to open new office in Pune later in 2022
news.para: "Recruiting starts now though alongside the organization’s rapidly growing teams in Gurgaon, Hyderabad and Bangalore," the Mountain View headquartered technology giant said in a statement.
